[Student "S"]
{With eleven cards in the "round" suits NORTH has a lot of playing strength. So when SOUTH bids 
a Limit Raise in \Hs NORTH wants to know about Aces.

RKCBlackwood tells him that SOUTH has two Aces plus the trump Queen, so NORTH can see that 6\H 
is practically a certainty.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "E:AK9842.KQT6.84.A T.9742.AJ5.Q9876 QJ73.AJ5.T632.K4 65.83.KQ97.JT532"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "4S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
1S pass 3S pass 4C pass 4H pass 4S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: E, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 0, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "0094373ad8de7f26ac0686fd1b8760023898f869adc392b3140464ce2ebb7ebf"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "advanced"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/roman_key_card"]
[Student "S"]
{EAST has interest in slam after she hears WEST's Limit Raise. 
BUT, she should not use Blackwood holding two quick losers in the \D 
suit.

Instead she makes a Control showing bid of 4\C. (Not Gerber since it didn't follow a NT bid.)

WEST cooperates by making a Control bid of 4\H.

EAST stops at 4\S because neither partner controls \Ds.}

